snippet.title: Following Einstein's Math - Something Strange Happens
snippet.description:
Following Einstein's Math - Something Strange Happens 

Dive into the fascinating world of Einstein's equations and discover the strange and mind-bending phenomena they predict! From time dilation and black holes to the warping of spacetime, Einstein's math has revolutionized our understanding of the universe. Join us as we explore the incredible and sometimes bizarre implications of his theories, and learn how they continue to shape modern physics. Watch now to unlock the mysteries of the cosmos!

Einstein's groundbreaking theories of relativity have fundamentally changed the way we understand the universe. His equations describe phenomena so strange and counterintuitive that they continue to fascinate scientists and the public alike. Here are some of the mind-boggling predictions and implications of Einstein's math:

1. **Time Dilation:**
   - According to the theory of special relativity, time slows down for objects moving at speeds close to the speed of light. This means that a spaceship traveling at near-light speed would experience time much more slowly than someone on Earth. This phenomenon has been confirmed by experiments with high-speed particles and precise atomic clocks.

2. **Length Contraction:**
   - Special relativity also predicts that objects moving at high speeds will appear shorter in the direction of their motion. This effect, called length contraction, becomes significant at speeds approaching the speed of light.

3. **Mass-Energy Equivalence:**
   - Einstein's famous equation, \(E = mc^2\), shows that mass and energy are interchangeable. This principle is the foundation of nuclear energy and explains why a small amount of mass can release a tremendous amount of energy.

4. **Black Holes:**
   - General relativity predicts the existence of black holes, regions of spacetime where gravity is so strong that nothing, not even light, can escape. The study of black holes has led to discoveries about event horizons, singularities, and the potential for wormholes.

5. **Gravitational Waves:**
   - Einstein's equations predicted that accelerating massive objects, like merging black holes or neutron stars, would create ripples in spacetime known as gravitational waves. These waves were first directly detected in 2015, opening a new era of observational astronomy.

6. **Warping of Spacetime:**
   - General relativity describes gravity not as a force, but as the curvature of spacetime caused by mass and energy. Massive objects like stars and planets warp the fabric of spacetime, causing the paths of objects (and light) to bend.

7. **Cosmic Time Travel:**
   - The warping of spacetime and the potential existence of wormholes suggest the theoretical possibility of time travel. While this remains speculative, Einstein's equations provide a mathematical framework for exploring these possibilities.

8. **The Expanding Universe:**
   - Einstein's equations, when applied to the universe as a whole, suggest that space itself is expanding. This discovery, confirmed by observations of distant galaxies, led to the development of the Big Bang theory.

9. **Cosmological Constant:**
   - Einstein introduced the cosmological constant to his equations to allow for a static universe, which he later called his "biggest blunder" after the discovery of the expanding universe. However, the concept has resurfaced in modern cosmology to explain dark energy, the mysterious force driving the accelerated expansion of the universe.

10. **Quantum Gravity:**
    - The incompatibility of general relativity with quantum mechanics suggests that a new theory, known as quantum gravity, is needed to fully understand the fundamental nature of spacetime. Efforts to reconcile these theories include approaches like string theory and loop quantum gravity.

Einstein's mathematical framework has not only provided profound insights into the nature of the cosmos but also continues to challenge and inspire physicists in their quest to understand the universe at its deepest level. Exploring these strange and fascinating phenomena reveals the true power and elegance of Einstein's theories, reshaping our view of reality itself.


 #EinsteinMath, #Relativity, #Physics, #TimeDilation, #BlackHoles, #Spacetime, #ScienceExplained, #CosmicPhenomena, #Astrophysics, #QuantumTheory

snippet.title: WSU: Space, Time, and Einstein with Brian Greene
snippet.description:
Join Brian Greene, acclaimed physicist and author, on a wild ride into the mind of Albert Einstein, revealing deep aspects of the world that defy everyday experience. Using a visually rich canvas of animations, Greene leads you through all the startling conclusions of special relativity, from time travel to space warps to E = mc2. In the span of 2+ hours, this short master class will change your conception of reality.

This is a mostly non-mathematical version of the WSU Master Class “Special Relativity with Brian Greene.” https://youtu.be/XFV2feKDK9E

snippet.title: The Richness of Time
snippet.description:
Join a physicist, a neuroscientist, and a linguist as they explore the deep enigmas of time. Time feels like it flows, but does it? Time seems to have a built-in direction, from past to future, but is that real or merely a quality imposed by the human brain? Time on earth elapses at a uniform rate, so why does the human experience of time seem so varied? How do various neurological afflictions change the perception of time? And underneath it all, how does human language impact our ability to think about time and fully experience its rich and mysterious contours?

PARTICIPANTS: Lera Boroditsky, Dean Buonomano

MODERATOR: Brian Greene

MORE INFO ABOUT THE PROGRAM AND 
PARTICIPANTS: https://www.worldsciencefestival.com/programs/the-richness-of-time/

This program is part of the BIG IDEAS SERIES, made possible with support from the JOHN TEMPLETON FOUNDATION.

snippet.title: A Matter of Time
snippet.description:
The nature of time is an age-old conundrum for physicists, philosophers, biologists and theologians. The Newtonian picture of time—a kind of cosmic clock that ticks off time in a manner that applies identically to everyone and everything—tightly aligns with our experience. But with special and general relativity, Einstein showed the fallacy inherent in experience: the rate at which time elapses depends on circumstance and environment. These discoveries raise even more basic, long-standing puzzles: What is time? Is it a fundamental feature of reality or something we humans impose on experience? Does time come into existence with the universe or does it transcend it? Why does time exist at all?

The World Science Festival gathers great minds in science and the arts to produce live and digital content that allows a broad general audience to engage with scientific discoveries. Our mission is to cultivate a general public informed by science, inspired by its wonder, convinced of its value, and prepared to engage with its implications for the future.

Subscribe to our YouTube Channel for all the latest from WSF.
Visit our Website: http://www.worldsciencefestival.com/
Like us on Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/worldsciencefestival
Follow us on twitter: https://twitter.com/WorldSciFest

Original Program Date: June 02 2013
MODERATOR: Ira Flatow
PARTICIPANTS: Paul Davies, Craig Callender, Tim Maudlin, Max Tegmark

Ira Flatow's Introduction 00:00

Participant Introductions 1:03

How did Einstein get involve with time? 3:36

What is the symmetry of time? 8:20

What was Einsteins concept of time? 10:09

Tim Maudlin has his own opinion on time. 12:42
 
How do you prove time dilation? 16:40

localized.title: A Matter of Time
localized.description:
The nature of time is an age-old conundrum for physicists, philosophers, biologists and theologians. The Newtonian picture of time—a kind of cosmic clock that ticks off time in a manner that applies identically to everyone and everything—tightly aligns with our experience. But with special and general relativity, Einstein showed the fallacy inherent in experience: the rate at which time elapses depends on circumstance and environment. These discoveries raise even more basic, long-standing puzzles: What is time? Is it a fundamental feature of reality or something we humans impose on experience? Does time come into existence with the universe or does it transcend it? Why does time exist at all?

The World Science Festival gathers great minds in science and the arts to produce live and digital content that allows a broad general audience to engage with scientific discoveries. Our mission is to cultivate a general public informed by science, inspired by its wonder, convinced of its value, and prepared to engage with its implications for the future.

snippet.title: Cosmology in Crisis? Confronting the Hubble Tension
snippet.description:
How fast is the universe expanding? Two prominent approaches are finding different answers, propelling cosmology toward a crisis. Wendy Freedman, a renowned astronomer who has spent decades seeking the expansion rate, joins Brian Greene to discuss the latest thinking on this so-called Hubble Tension.

snippet.title: Arctic Sinkholes I Full Documentary I NOVA I PBS
snippet.description:
In the Arctic, enormous releases of methane, a potent greenhouse gas, threaten the climate.

Colossal explosions shake a remote corner of the Siberian tundra, leaving behind massive sinkholes. In Alaska, a huge lake erupts with bubbles of inflammable gas. Scientists are discovering that these mystifying phenomena add up to a ticking time bomb, as long-frozen permafrost melts and releases vast amounts of methane, a potent greenhouse gas. What are the implications of these dramatic developments in the Arctic? Scientists and local communities alike are struggling to grasp the scale of the methane threat and what it means for our climate future.

Official Website: https://to.pbs.org/3AOUzLz

Chapters
00:00 Introduction
02:22 Giant Sinkhole in Siberia
05:54 Evidence of Methane in Sinkholes 
09:02 Alaskan Lake Bubbling
14:47 Effects of Permafrost Thaw on Climate 
17:26 Native Alaskan Solutions to Permafrost
21:37 Organic Matter Impacted by Permafrost
24:44 Greenhouse Gasses Emitted from Permafrost Thaw
33:37 Fossil Methane in Earth’s Crust
42:19 Arctic Regions are Sinking

snippet.title: Can We Cool the Planet? | Full Documentary I NOVA | PBS
snippet.description:
Scientists look to geoengineering and other methods to cool the planet.

Official Website: https://to.pbs.org/3lWpliq | #novapbs 

As global temperatures continue to rise, scientists are wondering if we need solutions that go beyond reducing emissions. From sucking carbon straight out of the air, to geoengineering our atmosphere to physically block out sunlight, to planting more than a trillion trees, the options may seem futuristic or tough to implement. But as time runs out on conventional solutions to climate change, scientists are asking the hard questions: Can new, sometimes controversial, solutions really work? And at what cost?

Chapters
00:00 Introduction
05:02 The Impact of Carbon Dioxide on the Atmosphere
12:15 Removing CO2 from the Atmosphere: Where Does it Go?
19:16 Innovations Made from Recycled Carbon Dioxide
24:33 How Carbon Dioxide Emissions Can Be Reduced to Net Zero?
34:41 Impacts of Solar Geoengineering
38:00 Can Trees Help Decrease CO2 in the Atmosphere?
46:05 Can Grasslands Help Decrease CO2 in the Atmosphere?
48:49 Conclusion

snippet.title: Polar Extremes: Ice Worlds | Full Documentary | NOVA | PBS
snippet.description:
Paleontologist Kirk Johnson explores the dynamic history—and future—of ice at the poles. (Aired February 5, 2020)

Official Website: https://to.pbs.org/3EUn0KC | #novapbs 

In this two-hour special, renowned paleontologist Kirk Johnson takes us on an epic adventure through time at the polar extremes of our planet. Following a trail of strange fossils found in all the wrong places—beech trees in Antarctica, hippo-like mammals in the Arctic—Johnson uncovers the bizarre history of the poles, from miles-high ice sheets to warm polar forests teeming with life. What caused such dramatic changes at the ends of the Earth? And what can the past reveal about our planet’s climate today—and in the future?

Chapters
00:00:00 Introduction
00:05:49 Hunting for Fossils on Islands near the North and South Poles
00:22:52 Fossil of New Dinosaur Species Found in Patagonia
00:29:04 Was Death Valley Always the Hottest Place on the Planet?
00:37:32 How Have Carbon Dioxide Levels Changed on Earth Over Time?
00:49:18 How Do Ice Sheets Form in Antarctica
00:56:47 How Did Life Persist Through the Ice Age?
01:11:29 Impacts of Rising Temperatures on Ice Cycles of the Planet
01:31:30 What Was the Warm World Like Before the Ice Age
01:43:04 This Cave Has Been Frozen for 100,000 Years
01:50:30 Conclusion

snippet.title: Hunt for the Oldest DNA | Full Documentary | NOVA | PBS
snippet.description:
Follow the quest to recover DNA millions of years old for the very first time.

Official Website: https://to.pbs.org/483Fzs7 | #novapbs 

For decades, scientists have tried to unlock the secrets of ancient DNA. But life’s genetic blueprint is incredibly fragile, and researchers have struggled to find DNA in fossils that could survive millions of years. Then, one maverick scientist had the controversial idea to look for DNA not in fossils or frozen ancient tissue – but in dirt. Join the hunt as scientists decipher the oldest DNA ever found, and reveal for the first time the genes of long-extinct creatures that once thrived in a warm, lush Arctic.

Chapters
00:00 Introduction
06:08 Challenges of Recovering Ancient DNA from Soil
22:36 Searching for Ancient Animal and Plant DNA in Greenland
37:59 Accurately Dating the Ancient DNA
43:03 How Did DNA Survive So Long?
45:23 What Was Earth Like Before the Ice Age?
48:15 Lessons Learned from the Pliocene

snippet.description:
조용히 내리는 비는 당신의 긴장을 풀고 깊은 잠을 줄 것입니다.

[빗소리와 수면의 관계]
빗소리를 들으면 뇌파 중 델타파에 에너지가 집중된다.
델타파는 깊은 수면에서 지배적인 뇌파입니다.
이 시점에서 뇌는 많은 치료적 성장 호르몬을 방출할 것입니다.
빗소리는 우리 몸의 자율신경을 자극하여 마음을 진정시키고 숙면에 도움을 줍니다.
백색소음의 자연스러운 소리 중 빗소리는 깊은 잠을 유도한다.
빗소리는 숙면 유도, 불면증 해소, 스트레스 감소,
집중력 향상 및 수면 장애 극복에 도움이 됩니다.
나는 당신에게 행복과 평화를 기원합니다.

🟢 인스타그램 - https://www.instagram.com/relaxingtimeforyou/
🟢 틱톡 - https://www.tiktok.com/@relaxingtimeforyou?lang=en-US
🟢 페이스북 - https://www.facebook.com/sdhjoong/

🎧 볼륨을 적절하게 조절하여 더 나은 소리를 냅니다.
.

🍀구독과 좋아요는 여러분의 따뜻한 마음입니다.
    영상제작에 큰 도움이 됩니다.
 https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCKptJ-XQRf_4X4ZY9Cr_75Q

🍀당신의 편안한 경험을 방해할 수 있으므로 내 채널의 비디오에 단어를 추가하지 않습니다.
영상 만드는 방법은 '비하인드'를 참고해주세요.
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=v7JUEk0Y3z0

🍀비디오 편집 및 장비
모든 콘텐츠는 내가 만들고 완성합니다.
비디오 및 오디오는 현장에서 직접 촬영 및 녹음됩니다.
드문 경우지만 After Effects에서 비디오/사진을 결합하여
새롭고 창의적인 것을 만드십시오.
 ◻️동영상: sony a6400, sony a6600, dgi air2로 촬영했습니다.
 ◻️오디오: 줌 h5n, 줌 h4n pro로 녹음하세요.
 ◻️소프트웨어: primierepro2020, 애프터 이펙트, 파이널컷으로 편집, 믹스 및 마스터링.

🍀면책 조항
"당신을 위한 편안한 시간" 채널은 수면 보조 채널이며 의학적 조언이나 치료를 대신할 수 없습니다.
심각한 질병이나 과로로 인한 수면 장애가 있는 경우에는 반드시 의사와 상담하십시오.

 🚫 경고 🚫
본인 채널의 릴랙싱 타임 영상 및 오디오의 무단 복제 및 재사용을 금합니다.
동영상 및 오디오를 무단으로 재사용하는 경우 YouTube 수익 정책 위반으로 제재를 받을 수 있습니다.
🚫 경고 🚫
'릴랙싱 타임 포 유' 채널의 영상 및 음성을 복사하거나 재사용하는 것을 금지합니다.
동영상 및 오디오를 무단으로 재사용하는 경우 YouTube 수익 정책 위반으로 제재를 받을 수 있습니다.

#편안한시간 #빗소리 #수면 #빗소리
숙면을 위한 빗소리, 편안한 비, 뇌우, 잠이 오는 빗소리,
집중력, 숙면, 수면 ASMR, 스트레스 해소,
불면증 해소, 명상, 요가, 힐링, 릴렉스,공부,시험공부
백색소음으로 집중력 향상 ,자연의소리,빗소리로 잠 잘자는법.

snippet.title: 🔴 5분만에 잠들기 - 잠 잘 오는 부드러운 빗소리 / 블랙스크린 24H / 수면에 최적화된 부드러운 빗소리 ASMR
snippet.description:
수면과 조용한 빗소리 간에는 긍정적인 관계가 있을 수 있습니다. 
일반적으로, 조용한 빗소리는 뇌파를 안정시키고 뇌를 진정시키는 효과가 있기 때문입니다. 
이러한 효과는 수면의 질을 향상시키고 잠재적으로 불면증 증상을 완화할 수 있습니다.

조용한 빗소리는 또한 백색 소음의 일종입니다. 
백색 소음은 무작위로 발생하는 소리들의 빈도수를 모두 포함하고 있으며, 이는 환경 소음을 차단하고, 뇌에 긍정적인 영향을 미치는 것으로 알려져 있습니다. 
이러한 효과는 뇌파를 안정시키고 집중력을 높이는 데 도움이 될 수 있습니다.
따라서, 조용한 빗소리는 수면을 촉진하는 데 도움이 되며, 불면증 증상을 완화하는 데 효과적일 수 있습니다. 

#블랙스크린 #빗소리 #자장가
🟢  SPOTIFY -https://open.spotify.com/album/4wAnN61QEwYKYu9d1A8mxf?utm_source=SendGrid&utm_medium=Email+&utm_campaign=website
🟢  INSTAGRAM - https://www.instagram.com/relaxingtimeforyou/
🟢  TIKTOK - https://www.tiktok.com/@relaxingtimeforyou?lang=ko-KR
🟢  FACEBOOK - https://www.facebook.com/sdhjoong/

🎧 볼륨을 알맞게 조절하시면 더 좋은 소리로 들을 수 있습니다. 

🍀구독과 좋아요는 당신의 따뜻한 마음입니다. 
    영상을 제작하는데 큰 힘이 됩니다.   
 https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCKptJ-XQRf_4X4ZY9Cr_75Q 

🍀내 채널에서는 휴식 경험을 방해할 수 있으므로 영상에 말을 추가하지 않습니다. 
비디오 제작 방법에 대해서 '비하인드 스토리'를 참고하세요.
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=v7JUEk0Y3z0

🍀VIDEO EDIT & EQUIPMENT
모든 콘텐츠는 제가 직접 만들고 완성합니다. 
비디오와 오디오는 현장에서 직접 촬영하고 녹음합니다.  
드문 경우지만, 나는 After Effects에서 비디오/사진을 결합하여 
새롭고 창의적인 것을 만듭니다. 
 ◻️비디오: sony a6400, sony a6600, dgi air2로 촬영합니다.
 ◻️오디오: zoom h5n, zoom h4n pro로 녹음합니다.
 ◻️소프트웨어: primierepro2020, after effect, finalcut으로 편집,믹싱,마스터링 합니다.

🍀DISCLAIMER
"Relaxing Time for you" 채널은 수면 보조 채널이며 의학적 조언이나 치료를 대체할 수 없습니다. 
심각한 질병이나 과로로 인한 수면장애는 반드시 의사와 상담하십시오. 

 🚫 경고 🚫
Relaxing Time for you 채널의 영상이나 오디오를 복사 또는 재사용하는 것을 금합니다. 
영상은 물론 오디오를 무단으로 재사용하면 유튜브 수익 정책 위반으로 제재를 받을 수 있습니다.
🚫 WARNING 🚫
Copying or reusing the video or audio of the "Relaxing Time for you" channel is prohibited.
Unauthorized reuse of video as well as audio may be subject to sanctions as a violation of YouTube's revenue policy.

snippet.description:
이 영상은 자연 그대로의 빗소리와 어두운 영상을 통해 깊고 편안한 수면을 유도합니다.

빗소리가 주는 효과:

스트레스 해소: 빗소리는 불안과 스트레스를 낮춰주는 효과가 있습니다.
자연스러운 잠들기: 빗소리는 자연의 속삭임과 같아 편안하게 잠들 수 있도록 도와줍니다.
수면 품질 향상: 빗소리는 깊은 잠을 유도하여 수면 품질을 높여줍니다.
집중력 향상: 빗소리는 집중력을 높여주는 효과가 있어 학습이나 업무에도 도움이 됩니다.
숙면 유도: 빗소리는 백색 소음의 역할을 하여, 깊고 편안한 숙면을 취할 수 있도록 돕습니다. 

🟢  SPOTIFY -https://open.spotify.com/album/4wAnN6...
🟢  INSTAGRAM - https://www.instagram.com/relaxingtim...
🟢  TIKTOK - https://www.tiktok.com/@relaxingtimef...
🟢  FACEBOOK - https://www.facebook.com/sdhjoong/

🎧 볼륨을 알맞게 조절하시면 더 좋은 소리로 들을 수 있습니다. 

🍀구독과 좋아요는 당신의 따뜻한 마음입니다. 
    영상을 제작하는데 큰 힘이 됩니다.   
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCKptJ-XQRf_4X4ZY9Cr_75Q   

🍀내 채널에서는 휴식 경험을 방해할 수 있으므로 영상에 말을 추가하지 않습니다. 
비디오 제작 방법에 대해서 '비하인드 스토리'를 참고하세요.
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=v7JUEk0Y3z0

🍀VIDEO EDIT & EQUIPMENT
모든 콘텐츠는 제가 직접 만들고 완성합니다. 
비디오와 오디오는 현장에서 직접 촬영하고 녹음합니다.  
드문 경우지만, 나는 After Effects에서 비디오/사진을 결합하여 
새롭고 창의적인 것을 만듭니다. 
 ◻️비디오: sony a6400, sony a6600, dgi air2로 촬영합니다.
 ◻️오디오: zoom h5n, zoom h4n pro로 녹음합니다.
 ◻️소프트웨어: primierepro2020, after effect, finalcut으로 편집,믹싱,마스터링 합니다.

🍀DISCLAIMER
"Relaxing Time for you" 채널은 수면 보조 채널이며 의학적 조언이나 치료를 대체할 수 없습니다. 
심각한 질병이나 과로로 인한 수면장애는 반드시 의사와 상담하십시오.

snippet.description:
이 영상은 어두운 화면과 부드러운 빗소리를 제공하여 불면증, 숙면, 휴식에 도움을 줍니다.

이는 뇌파를 알파파로 변화시켜 편안함을 유도하고, 불안감과 스트레스를 낮추는 효과를 가져옵니다.

결론적으로 빗소리는 다양한 심리적 효과를 가지고 있으며, 건강과 삶의 질 향상에 도움을 줄 수 있습니다.

snippet.title: Rainy Night on the Mountain with Crackling Fireplace for Sleeping, Relax, Study, Meditate
snippet.description:
Nestled atop a misty mountain, a cozy wooden cabin stood surrounded by ancient pines. Rain cascaded down in a soothing rhythm, punctuated by occasional flashes of lightning that illuminated the rugged landscape. Inside the cabin, a crackling fireplace cast a warm glow, creating a stark contrast to the storm raging outside.

The cabin was a refuge, a sanctuary from the harsh elements. The rain tapped gently on the windows, creating a symphony of nature's lullaby. The occasional rumble of thunder added a dramatic touch to the peaceful scene.

A lone figure sat by the fire, mesmerized by the dancing flames. The warmth of the fire enveloped them, chasing away the chill of the rainy night. Outside, the world was wild and untamed, but inside, there was only peace and serenity.

As the storm raged on, the figure wrapped themselves in a cozy blanket and closed their eyes, lulled into a peaceful sleep by the soothing sounds of the rain and the crackling fire. In that moment, there was no worry, no stress, only the simple joy of being surrounded by nature's beauty.

When morning came, the storm had passed, leaving behind a glistening world washed clean by the rain. The sun peeked through the clouds, casting a golden light over the mountain landscape. The cabin stood silent and serene, a testament to the beauty and power of nature.

And so, as the day began anew, the cabin stood as a beacon of warmth and shelter, a reminder that even in the midst of life's storms, there is always a place of peace and beauty to be found..

Hope you all enjoy it!
------------------------------------------------------
► Preparation of this Ambience:

Software used:
- Blender 3D
- Adobe Photoshop
- Adobe After Effects
-----------------------------------------------------

Many thanks to everyone for listening and for leaving your comment.

If you want to make suggestions please feel free to do so in the comments

----------------------------------------
We are staying at a cozy hotel in the mountains. The gentle rain and thunder is soothing us to sleep. Rain sound for sleeping is a great way to relax and beat insomnia

Equipment:
FujiFilm X-T3
Zoom H2N Handy Recorder

Created & Edited with After Effects and Premier Pro


#rain #asmr #rainsounds

🔴YOUTUBE REVIEW TEAM PLEASE READ:🔴
With the help of @YouTubeLiaison Matt Koval our channel is re-monetised after we have explained to Matt Koval how we make our videos.
On top of that we also got in touch with YouTube Partner Support [7-0994000030814] who after reviewing our channel wrote:
"On our last email we discussed that an appeal was sent to our specialists to take a look at your concern wherein your channel was demonetized. A decision has been made regarding that appeal and I've got some good news for you.
Based on the review, your channel now follows YouTube's Monetization Policies and has been approved to monetize."

Relaxing Ambience is a team of creative videographers around the world. We do not add commentary throughout our calming nature videos as it can detract from the relaxation experience. 

We create all of our own content. Videos and Audio are recorded out in the nature. Sometimes we will combine our videos/photos in After Effects to create something different and unique. 

🎥Here is us showing how we make our videos: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AfZ8EfNG4Cw

We edit, mix, & master audio in Adobe Audition & edit video with Adobe After Effects 7 Premier Pro. We currently film with a Sony a6000, Fujifilm X-T2 & X-T3, GoPro Hero 7 Black. We record audio with a Zoom H2N.

Each video typically takes at least 24 hours to create. This includes: 
☑️ Filming video & recording audio on location
☑️ Editing the video & audio
☑️ Final edit & master


🔴DISCLAIMER:

Please note that loud sounds can potentially damage your hearing. When playing one of our recordings, if you cannot have a conversation over the sound without raising your voice, the sound may be too loud for your ears. Please do not place speakers right next to a baby’s ears. If you have difficulty hearing or hear ringing in your ears, please immediately discontinue listening to the white noise sounds and consult an audiologist or your physician. 

The sounds provided by this Youtube channel are for entertainment purposes only and are not a treatment for sleep disorders or tinnitus. If you have significant difficulty sleeping on a regular basis, experience fitful/restless sleep, or feel tired during the day, please consult your physician. 

All material in this video is original and personally recorded by us.

Caring for Your Soul The Great Benefits of "Hearing the Rain" in Your Calmness
The bustle of the city chokes you. Sometimes you don't know how to overcome the stress of your body and mind. At that time, scientists will give you advice. The sound of rain is soothing and calms the tired and fearful mind.
